Derek J. Kerr 

		
		EVP and CFO, 

	
		 American Airlines Group Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 04/27/2017 



Executive Summary
Derek Kerr was appointed Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at US Airways Group in January 2009, and retained his position following the 2013 merger between US Airways and American. Kerr is responsible for US Airways' corporate finance, financial planning and analysis, accoun 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Kerr is married. He and his wife, Carolyn, have two children.
They live in Scottsdale, Arizona. 
Current Focus

Building trust: According to an April 2017 Dallas News article, American Airlines is taking the rare step of offering a mid-contract raise to its roughly 37,000 pilots and flight attendants after months of simmering ten 
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1965.
Kerr earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Aeronautical Engineering from the University of Michigan (1982-1986). 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Board of Trustees, Phoenix Zoo
Former Member, Advisory Board, CFOWorld 
Donations and Philanthropy

In 2009 he gave $1,000 to Pennsylvania Senator Arlen Specter's unsuccessful 2010 re-election campaign (after switching parties, he was defeated in the Democratic primary).
