Executive Profile
Derek J. Kerr  Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President, American Airlines Group Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 5 different industries.52$4,190,982As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Derek J. Kerr has been the Chief Financial Officer of American Airlines, Inc. since December 2013 and serves as its Executive Vice President and Principal Accounting Officer. Mr. Kerr oversees financial planning and analysis, corporate finance and treasury functions, purchasing, controller and audit functions and investor relations. He has been Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of American Airlines Group Inc. since December 9, 2013 and served as ... its Principal Accounting Officer since December 9, 2013. Mr. Kerr is responsible for oversight of all financial areas, including financial planning and analysis, corporate finance and treasury functions, purchasing, controller and audit functions and investor relations. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of US Airways, Inc. since September 27, 2005 and serves as its Executive Vice President and Principal Accounting Officer. He served as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of America West Holdings Corp since September 2002 and served as its Chief Accounting Officer. He served in various financial planning and analysis positions with Northwest Airlines. Mr. Kerr served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of US Airways Group, Inc. since January 2009 and 2005 respectively and served as its Principal Accounting Officer. He was responsible for all corporate financial functions including Treasury, Accounting, Financial Planning and Analysis, Tax, Risk Management, Strategic Planning and Investor Relations. He served as Senior Vice President of US Airways Inc. since September 27, 2005. Mr. Kerr served as Senior Vice President of US Airways Group, Inc. from September 2002 to January 2009 and its Chief Financial Officer since September 2002 and also served as its Chief Accounting Officer. Mr. Kerr served as Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President of US Airways, LLC (formerly, America West Airlines Inc.) since September 2002 and its Principal Accounting Officer. Mr. Kerr joined America West Airlines Inc. as Senior Director of Financial Planning since joining in April 1996. He served as Vice President of Financial Planning and Analysis at US Airways, LLC since May 1998. Since February 2002, he served as Senior Vice President of Financial Planning and Analysis at US Airways, LLC with responsibility for purchasing and fuel administration. He was a flight test coordinator/control engineer with Northrop Corporation’s B-2 Division. He is an executive sponsor for African American Diversity Network. He serves on the board of directors for the Fiesta Bowl and Dallas Regional Chamber. He sits on the board of directors of the Phoenix Zoo and participates in alumni activities associated with the University of Michigan. He is a national trustee for the Boys & Girls Clubs of America. Mr. Kerr received the Arizona Chief Financial Officer of the Year Award in 2007. In 2013, Institutional Investor ranked US Airways as one of America’s Most Honored Companies, naming him to the 2013 All-America Executive Team. He has won several financial management awards and was named Arizona's Chief Financial Officer of the Year by the Arizona Chapter of Financial Executive International (FEI). He was selected from a field of nominees throughout Arizona, who realized significant achievements in finance and accounting. Mr. Kerr holds a Master of Business Administration in finance and a Bachelor of Science in Aeronautical Engineering from the University of Michigan.Read Full Background




